Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.86,0:00:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The dreams embraced by a single life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.86,0:00:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}are boundless beyond even the stars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.87,0:00:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The dreams that we foster over time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.88,0:00:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}are waiting for the moment{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}when we come upon them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.55,0:00:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The words we exchange{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}make our hearts tremble,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.56,0:00:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and a chance meeting{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}could change the future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.23,0:01:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}People, no matter who they are,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}as they pursue their dreams,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.51,0:01:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}have the courage to travel new paths.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.18,0:01:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}As we leave behind a living{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}testament of our journey,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.52,0:01:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}the Galaxy Railways on which{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}we travel continue ever on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.54,0:01:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The Wanderung Meteor Swarm...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.55,0:01:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}It roams through space over{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}a several-thousand-year cycle,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.05,0:01:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}destroying everything in its path.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.22,0:01:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Also called the Wandering Devil.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.56,0:02:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Common Front"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.85,0:02:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Picking up the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Wanderung Meteor Swarm on radar.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.52,0:02:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The observational data has a margin\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of error of 0.75. Contact in 780 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.19,0:02:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Spectrum optical analysis is making out\N{\c&He1e1e1&}75% of the constituent elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.29,0:02:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm forwarding the data.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.53,0:02:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Acknowledged. Watch out for any\N{\c&He1e1e1&}gravitational field fluctuations
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.30,0:02:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}in the area, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.20,0:02:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, aren't you done yet, {\i1}Meteor-chans!?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.20,0:02:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're all ready over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.37,0:02:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's hurry up and smash this thing,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Spica {\i1}Kitten-chans!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.87,0:02:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Those guys are the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.21,0:02:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Who are they calling kittens?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.54,0:02:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Focus on your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.85,0:02:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Our mission is to protect Central Station\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from the meteor swarm's approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.55,0:02:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- R- roger.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- R- roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.22,0:02:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're as rigid as ever, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.32,0:02:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And here it's been so long\N{\c&He1e1e1&}since we've worked together.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.56,0:03:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Once we get the job done,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}join me for a drink, Julia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.49,0:03:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It'll be my treat. How does that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.50,0:03:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.50,0:03:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}She doesn't like you, huh Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.50,0:03:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You stay out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.84,0:03:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Wanderung Meteor Swarm approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.19,0:03:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Now analyzing data. Vega Platoon,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}please stand by until further notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.86,0:03:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}180 seconds to contact with the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.86,0:03:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The number of meteors that will have to be\N{\c&He1e1e1&}eliminated or destroyed is approximately...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.86,0:03:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Iron Berger{\i0} is moving\N{\c&He1e1e1&}into attack position!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.20,0:03:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Prepare to intercept!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.44,0:03:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Once the main cannons and all turrets\N{\c&He1e1e1&}are deployed, lower the track shields!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.88,0:03:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Vega Platoon, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.55,0:03:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We still have not finished\N{\c&He1e1e1&}analyzing the data.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.05,0:03:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Wait until we determine the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}precise manner to dispatch them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.88,0:04:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sorry, but we're going\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to dispose of them our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.82,0:04:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- Murase!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.22,0:04:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't let up! Fire! Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.24,0:04:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Cease fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.25,0:04:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.60,0:05:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The first wave of the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Wanderung Meteor Swarm has been evaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.27,0:05:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We've managed to prevent any\N{\c&He1e1e1&}damage to the station. However...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.87,0:05:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.54,0:05:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah, we got them!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.88,0:05:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.88,0:05:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yahoo! We kicked it large!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.55,0:05:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What was that supposed to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.55,0:05:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What do you mean?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}That's the way we do things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.89,0:05:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We pummeled them even\N{\c&He1e1e1&}more royally than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.23,0:05:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is that so? You haven't\N{\c&He1e1e1&}changed since then, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.23,0:05:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I've had it with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.91,0:05:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Apparently, the way we do things\N{\c&He1e1e1&}doesn't sit too well with her, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.92,0:05:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Now observing the second wave,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.32,0:05:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and main body of the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Wanderung Meteor Swarm,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.92,0:05:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}which will approach Central Station\N{\c&He1e1e1&}once again in six hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.26,0:05:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We, Sirius Platoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.73,0:05:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}will be taking over for Vega Platoon\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in a joint mission with Spica Platoon
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.26,0:06:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Particle warpspeed generators\N{\c&He1e1e1&}reading normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.87,0:06:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Orbital communications radar\N{\c&He1e1e1&}reading normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.87,0:06:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One{\i0} moving to launch position.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.21,0:06:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ascent Float lock confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.21,0:06:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We leave at once,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to safeguard Central Station!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.55,0:06:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.95,0:06:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Energy normal. Pressure within the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}boiler is rising. Cylinder valves open.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.56,0:06:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Engage main circuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.89,0:06:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.56,0:06:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Systems all green!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.90,0:06:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One,{\i0} move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.91,0:06:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I knew there was no way those two\N{\c&He1e1e1&}were going to get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.58,0:06:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But Captain Julia and Captain Murase used\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to be assigned to the same platoon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.59,0:06:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}They must be old acquaintances.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.92,0:06:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Then, those two used to see each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.92,0:06:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you talking about?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}It's not like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.92,0:07:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's refrain from gossiping.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.86,0:07:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.20,0:07:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The Wanderung Meteor Swarm's second wave\N{\c&He1e1e1&}will approach in three hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.87,0:07:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}According to our observations,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.04,0:07:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}the second wave will be on a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}much larger scale than the first wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.55,0:07:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This region of Cassiopeia's orbit\N{\c&He1e1e1&}will be the point
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.58,0:07:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}where the Wanderung Meteor Swarm\N{\c&He1e1e1&}makes its closest approach,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.22,0:07:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and should be the last and\N{\c&He1e1e1&}most difficult part of this mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.89,0:07:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I anticipate that we will have\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to destroy a great deal of the meteors,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.22,0:07:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and I will be expecting everyone\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from both platoons to act swiftly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.56,0:07:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}During this mission,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you will all follow my orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.57,0:07:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sirius Platoon, you will act under\N{\c&He1e1e1&}my orders, not Captain Bulge's.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.40,0:07:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I will not allow any exceptions,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}under any circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.58,0:07:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Now then, we will call this mission\N{\c&He1e1e1&}"Operation Wanderung Clean Sweep."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.58,0:07:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Everyone, before the mission\N{\c&He1e1e1&}gets underway,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.08,0:07:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}do a final check on your stations.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.25,0:08:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}U- um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.19,0:08:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.19,0:08:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}When you say you won't\N{\c&He1e1e1&}allow any exceptions,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.32,0:08:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}does that mean even\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in emergency situations?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.19,0:08:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We could at least\N{\c&He1e1e1&}use our own judgment...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.86,0:08:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Like I said, follow my orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.20,0:08:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.86,0:08:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Not that I'm adopting the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}line of a certain idiot captain,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.73,0:08:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}but this is my way of doing things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.21,0:08:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's no wonder she doesn't get\N{\c&He1e1e1&}along with Vega Platoon, like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.22,0:08:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why don't you give\N{\c&He1e1e1&}those shoulders a rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.22,0:08:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're too late.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm not going to change. No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.56,0:08:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ever since back then, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.90,0:08:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.24,0:08:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's being pulled in\N{\c&He1e1e1&}by the star's gravity!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.58,0:09:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If it keeps going like that,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the train is in danger of melting!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.85,0:09:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Even with {\i1}Southern Cross,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.18,0:09:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}we can't get close enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.85,0:09:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Julia, hurry up and finish analyzing\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the eruption pattern of those prominences!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.85,0:09:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sorry, but I need\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a little more time, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.52,0:09:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I can't wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.52,0:09:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Murase!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.53,0:09:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Wait, Murase!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.19,0:09:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.20,0:09:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll have all the data together\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in a moment! Wait until then!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.53,0:09:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I told you, I can't wait!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm going to do whatever I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.87,0:09:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm coming to save you, right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.91,0:10:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If only I had completed analyzing\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that data sooner back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.81,0:10:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}we could have kept\N{\c&He1e1e1&}casualties to a minimum.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.92,0:10:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}And on top of that,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Murase was wounded...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.59,0:10:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's why I swore\N{\c&He1e1e1&}right then and there
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.92,0:10:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}that I wouldn't let anyone else get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.26,0:10:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thanks for the advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.27,0:10:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}While you're at it,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}give Murase some advice, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.94,0:10:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Tell him to stop being such an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.94,0:10:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll pass that along.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.94,0:10:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, we're out of booze here!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Bring some more over here, quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.95,0:10:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}R- right, coming right up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.62,0:10:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Where does she get off saying she\N{\c&He1e1e1&}can't serve together with Vega Platoon!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.32,0:10:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Up hers!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.29,0:10:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If we hadn't fired when we did,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sure it would have been bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.66,0:10:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.30,0:11:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We've got to be strong. No matter\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the time, no matter what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.23,0:11:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah. Gotta be strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.57,0:11:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No matter the time, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.24,0:11:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Even when doing {\i1}it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.57,0:11:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah, even when doing {\i1}it!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.26,0:11:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We will now commence\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Operation Wanderung Clean Sweep!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.94,0:11:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Wanderung Meteor Swarm approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.28,0:11:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Transmit to the Space Eagles:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.28,0:11:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Spica Platoon fighters,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}fan out to the right;
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.48,0:11:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sirius Platoon fighters, to the left!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.95,0:11:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- Copy.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.90,0:12:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Deploy main cannons.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.57,0:12:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Prepare to intercept.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Lower track shields.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.92,0:12:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Commence fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.92,0:12:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Copy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.94,0:12:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.60,0:12:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.61,0:12:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Copy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.22,0:13:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That was big!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.22,0:13:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.23,0:13:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The mission is proceeding\N{\c&He1e1e1&}according to schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.36,0:13:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It looks like we'll finish up this time\N{\c&He1e1e1&}without any incidents, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.90,0:13:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.57,0:13:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.58,0:13:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm good and drunk.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I must be slipping.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.58,0:13:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Maybe you're just getting older.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.92,0:13:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't be ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.22,0:13:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're about a hundred years too early\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to be treating me like an old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.60,0:13:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.60,0:13:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I've identified a body in the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}meteor swarm that wasn't in our data.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.60,0:13:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It could be because of an irregularity
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.24,0:13:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}caused by gravitational\N{\c&He1e1e1&}field fluctuations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.27,0:13:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What!? How in the world can that be!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.22,0:14:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is this? The meteors\N{\c&He1e1e1&}are increasing, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.89,0:14:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's going on?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}This wasn't in our data.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.56,0:14:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is this? There are\N{\c&He1e1e1&}too many irregularities.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.90,0:14:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ai, give us some data.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.57,0:14:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's no use. The gravitational field\N{\c&He1e1e1&}fluctuations are creating irregularities,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.30,0:14:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and I can't predict\N{\c&He1e1e1&}what course it's taking!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.91,0:14:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The fourth car has sustained\N{\c&He1e1e1&}damage to it left side.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.91,0:14:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If this keeps up,\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One{\i0} is not going to last!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.58,0:14:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.60,0:14:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Damn...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.60,0:15:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you doing, Yuuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.87,0:15:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I told you to not to leave your post\N{\c&He1e1e1&}during this mission! Follow my orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.54,0:15:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The data analysis will be\N{\c&He1e1e1&}complete in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.98,0:15:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Until then, stand by at your post!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.21,0:15:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.22,0:15:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I can't just let this crisis\N{\c&He1e1e1&}play itself out in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.55,0:15:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm going to do what I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.89,0:15:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I'm going to do whatever I can!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.23,0:15:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain, there's a giant comet!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.91,0:15:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.91,0:15:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's so huge...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.24,0:15:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Meteor approaching from the left at\N{\c&He1e1e1&}8 o'clock! We can't get out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.58,0:15:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.58,0:15:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, don't let your guard down!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.92,0:15:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Murase!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.26,0:15:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Looks like nothing's going to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}get done without us here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.60,0:15:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain Murase!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.87,0:16:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you so scared of that pebble for?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}We'll put it away right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.87,0:16:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ready the main guns!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.87,0:16:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We'll get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.21,0:16:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Watch this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.21,0:16:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.22,0:16:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's primarily composed of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}superhardened cosmotium crystal,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.62,0:16:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}the hardest substance in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.22,0:16:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.56,0:16:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you hit it wrong, you won't destroy it,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you'll just alter its path.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.56,0:16:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It will just cause more damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.23,0:16:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Give me 150 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.56,0:16:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.90,0:16:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No matter how hard a substance is,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.97,0:16:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}there must be someplace where\N{\c&He1e1e1&}its molecular bonds are weaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.90,0:16:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If we can blast it at that key point,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}we might be able to destroy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.57,0:16:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Might be able to"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.91,0:16:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't be ridiculous! You expect us\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to wait for that sort of nonsense!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.24,0:16:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is what I can do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.25,0:16:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}150 seconds, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.25,0:16:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.26,0:16:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.92,0:17:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bulge!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.86,0:17:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I know.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.19,0:17:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Couple {\i1}Big One{\i0} up to {\i1}Iron Berger.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.16,0:17:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're going to forward our energy\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to their main cannon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.20,0:17:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.87,0:17:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ai, analyze the comet's structure using\N{\c&He1e1e1&}all sensors. Do not overlook any data.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.87,0:17:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.87,0:17:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Maggie, Shelley, give priority\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to gathering data, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.21,0:17:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.21,0:17:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Leave this to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.88,0:17:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You take care of getting the data.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.55,0:17:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.89,0:17:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bring {\i1}Big One{\i0} alongside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.55,0:17:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Coming alongside...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.89,0:17:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Engage energy supply probes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.22,0:17:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.90,0:17:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Energy charge at 80%.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.64,0:17:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Deploy particle cannon\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to firing position.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.58,0:17:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Target scope open.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.19,0:18:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Energy charge at 150%.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.86,0:18:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Giant comet approaching\N{\c&He1e1e1&}at 400 spacekilos.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.53,0:18:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}380 spacekilos.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.20,0:18:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Where? Where is it?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Where's its weak spot?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.87,0:18:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Our lighting is about to cut out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.54,0:18:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Energy charge, 200%.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.88,0:18:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is it time yet, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.21,0:18:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Calm down. Have faith in her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.22,0:18:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Giant comet approaching\N{\c&He1e1e1&}at 280 spacekilos.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.56,0:18:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Visual confirmation on the comet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.89,0:18:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's so huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.23,0:18:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All fighters, withdraw for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.23,0:18:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- Copy.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- Copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.57,0:18:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Comet approaching at 180 spacekilos.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.51,0:19:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It has passed the last line of defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.52,0:19:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We can't wait any longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.19,0:19:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Firing point identified!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.86,0:19:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Main cannon ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.19,0:19:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Aim for point E-35 N-14!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Tolerance is within 0.42!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.86,0:19:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Copy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.20,0:19:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Aiming at point E-35 N-14...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.54,0:19:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Tolerance within 0.42...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.54,0:19:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.24,0:20:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain, are you okay? Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.24,0:20:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What happened to the comet?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.58,0:20:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain Bulge! Is everyone all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.91,0:20:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah. We're all okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.58,0:20:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ah, it's a good thing\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I didn't bet on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.91,0:20:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.58,0:20:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It looks like it's snowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.25,0:20:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We did it, Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.92,0:20:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Looks like I owe you another one.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.26,0:20:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.60,0:20:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why did you come to help me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.60,0:20:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.60,0:20:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Would I be trying too hard\N{\c&He1e1e1&}if I said my scar started itching?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.61,0:20:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You haven't changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.61,0:20:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Also...
